data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func`, not `Expression<Func>`

Your manual expression tree won't compile. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The new overload accepts a regular delegate, so conditional logic works inline ŌĆö no more `Expression.Call`/`Expression.Lambda` gymnastics.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now uniquified & nested paths changed

**Two sub-changes:**

- **Same-named properties** across complex types (e.g. `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get a disambiguating suffix instead of silently sharing a column. This will generate a migration that renames columns.
- **Nested complex types** now use the **full path**: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was just `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix ŌĆö pin the old column names explicitly:**

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin each property:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");   // old name without full path
```

Or, if you're OK with the new names, just generate a migration and apply it ŌĆö no code change needed, but **verify the rename doesn't break existing queries/reports**.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. This carries the **redacted** SQL for safe logging.

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)        // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the real SQL
    }
}
```

Update every method in your implementation to add this parameter.
